{"title":"BrakeAce Wireless Braking Analysis Tool promises to make you a faster rider","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/07/01/brakeace-wireless-braking-analysis-tool-promises-to-make-you-a-faster-rider/","date":1625144672000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p>Do you want to descend faster without getting fitter? Founder of BrakeAce, Dr Matt Miller, says his new wireless braking analysis tool can help you do just that. The sensor replaces your brake mount, positioned between the fork/frame and the caliper; here, it measures all aspects of braking, feeding that data into an App that highlights sections of the trail where you could brake more effectively to carry a higher average speed. Here’s what we know so far.</p><p><span><iframe width=\"696\" height=\"392\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/P06Pwm3IVr4?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\" ezoid=\"0.6596321794046835\"></iframe></span></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper.jpg\" alt=\"brakeace wireless braking analysis tool for mountainbiking caliper sensor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"799\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-1068x711.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-631x420.jpg 631w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb20 src ng ngcb20 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-1068x711.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084525/brakeace-sensor-sram-code-calliper-631x420.jpg 631w\"></a></p><p>Founder Matt says BrakeAce is currently being tested by some of the biggest companies and fastest riders in the world. “Happy Customers” include Specialized, Hope and Stan’s NoTubes. The recent EWS in Val di Fassa recorded the closest ever men’s racing in series history. Thus, there’s no wonder athletes and their supporting brands are constantly looking for marginal gains.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score.jpg\" alt=\"brakeace app interface braking data analysis tool\" width=\"1200\" height=\"674\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score-297x167.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score-800x449.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score-120x67.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084506/brakeace-app-interface-shows-braking-data-flow-score-768x431.jpg 768w,https://