,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084519/brakeace-flow-score-pro-versus-beginner-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>So, what does it actually measure? A heap of things, actually. It takes a measurement 100 times per second on braking intensity, modulation, duration, and rotor temperature. All data are sent to the BrakeAce App, which will provide the rider with a “Flow Score” for their run. The Flow Score gives you an easy to understand metric for how effectively and efficiently you used your front and rear brake to carry speed down the track.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-m