ontent/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-297x184.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-800x495.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-120x74.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-768x476.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-696x431.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-1068x661.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-678x420.jpg 678w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/01084536/brakeace-universal-mount-any-rotor-compatibility-356x220.jpg 356w\"></a></p><p>The sensor design is patent pending. As it replaces the usual brake caliper mount, and takes up a fair bit of space, it does require that you up-size your rotor by 20mm from minimum (that alone will likely improve your braking efficiency). This shouldn’t be an issue for most forks but you will definitely need to check that your frame has sufficient clearance to run a bigger